                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d329">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.002/4.</note>
                <head>[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-07-20T12:00:00-04:49">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">July</hi> 20, 1911—12 <hi rend="smallcaps"
                                >noon</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The minister reports cabinet changes that will further injure status of the
                    present administration. He was advised yesterday by the Haitian Government that
                    the cities of St. Marc and Gonaives would be bombarded; he protested against
                    such action unless carried out in accordance with The Hague convention.</p>
            </div>
